I ordered the Assam fish tail and really enjoyed it. It had a nice sour and tangy kick, full of flavor. The fried chicken was crispy and paired perfectly with the sauce, which was delicious. The spinach with three eggs, however, was a bit too soupy for my taste.

Service was great! The three ladies taking my order were very patient and attentive.

Fish soup and porridge stall, one of the Atar stall among all and in any coffee shop. Fish soup is nice, but it's less Fish and it's Very expensive.  Less than 10 pieces and small pieces.  $15 plus $0.70 rice. **Dear Ding Ji noodles stall, pls bring back the Yellow noodles Soup! Realy gd and unique so old sch taste**

There is this existing noodle stall(by ding ji) aka ban mian(formerly used to sell yellow soup noodle and also mixed pork congee. BOTH ALSO NICE! Especially the yellow noodles soup reminds me of mum's old sch noodles, which unable to get it at any food stall in spore.  Visited regularly before and during covid period. But then 2.5yrs ago suddenly removed *Yellow noodles* instead replaced it with "ban mian flour noodles*, Not good, lost it characteristic. Since then my family and i had stopped buying. Recently hubby try to buy the noodles, soup still ok *BUT Overall taste is lost..taste typical Cheena chinese ban mian, sigh!*
Anyway shall check out if congee still taste as fine.
*Praise the man behind the stall is always friendly and accomodating thou not smiling but he is ok.
